Package: ecobz
Version: 1.0.0
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Essential: no
Depends: bash (>= 4.0), apt, systemd
Maintainer: Ecobz <dev@ecobz.io>
Description: Ubuntu Server Auto-Configuration CLI
ecobz is a command-line tool for quick and recommended
configuration of Ubuntu servers. It handles:

- System update & upgrade
- Hostname & timezone configuration
- Essential package installation
- Automatic security updates (unattended-upgrades)
- UFW firewall configuration
- NTP time synchronization
- Swap file creation
- Sysctl kernel optimisation
  .
  Run `sudo ecobz server-config` after installation to
  auto-configure your server with one command.
